When DesktopGL games are launched from Steam, a couple issues can happen (tested on Windows only):
- mouse coordinates have the top left corner of the screen for origin when using windowed mode;
- `Viewport` (or possibly the backbuffer) size is 50% smaller (most probably related to the DPI issue);

This is not related to the overlay. Launching the exact same build from the install folder instead of the Steam client resolves these issues.

Follow up to #4452

I also moved `OggStream` to the `Audio` namespace to have every OpenAL bits under the same one.

@tomspilman @KonajuGames
